FILE PHOTO:President Vaclav Havel and his wife Olga Havlova at their Hradecek cottage, August 18, 1995.Vaclav Havel died on Sunday, Dec. 18, 2011, aged 75. Havel, a dissident playwright jailed by Communists, became Czechoslovak and than Czech president and a symbol of peace and freedom after bringing down communism in Czechoslovakia by leading bloodless "Velvet Revolution". CTK Photo/Jan Trestik
